cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with improving performance in computer vision tasks using deep learning and post-processing techniques. Specifically, it introduces a new neural architecture for human pose estimation, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic methods, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of deep learning and neural networks suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation on large-scale datasets suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
